WEBVTT

00:00:03.630 --> 00:00:06.230
<i>The weather is nice this autumn,</i>

00:00:06.230 --> 00:00:09.860
<i>and the carrots
taste even better.</i>

00:00:09.860 --> 00:00:12.900
<i>We ran the Takarazuka Kinen
since I last wrote.</i>

00:00:13.920 --> 00:00:15.720
{\an9}Air Groove

00:00:23.510 --> 00:00:25.790
<i>I can't make it…</i>

00:00:29.210 --> 00:00:31.940
<i>Silence Suzuka manged to keep her lead!</i>

00:00:31.940 --> 00:00:34.470
<i>The favorite, Air Groove, has come in third!</i>

00:00:34.470 --> 00:00:36.760
<i>Team Spica has been doing extremely well.</i>

00:00:36.760 --> 00:00:40.750
<i>Yes, people should keep their eye
on Team Spica in the upcoming races.</i>

00:00:42.550 --> 00:00:45.770
<i>I just become more and more
enamored with Suzuka-san.</i>

00:00:46.530 --> 00:00:47.270
<i>And…</i>

00:00:48.770 --> 00:00:52.900
<i>Mejiro McQueen-san has joined Team Spica.</i>

00:00:52.900 --> 00:00:55.180
Everyone, welcome her.

00:00:55.180 --> 00:00:57.660
Welcome to Team Spica.

00:00:58.330 --> 00:01:00.320
<i>This seems familiar.</i>

00:01:01.250 --> 00:01:02.500
Nice to have you.

00:01:05.910 --> 00:01:07.430
What are you doing?

00:01:08.060 --> 00:01:09.710
Let your guard down, huh?

00:01:09.710 --> 00:01:11.210
I'm going to get you.

00:01:10.500 --> 00:01:12.980
{\an8}Stop it!

00:01:11.570 --> 00:01:13.580
We've got ourselves another troublemaker.

00:01:13.580 --> 00:01:15.730
What do you mean, "another"?!

00:01:15.730 --> 00:01:18.720
Are you sure you should be
the one saying that, Scarlet?

00:01:18.720 --> 00:01:21.220
{\an8}That's rich coming from you!

00:01:19.570 --> 00:01:22.930
<i>She gets along especially well
with Gold Ship-san.</i>

00:01:22.930 --> 00:01:24.850
<i>It feels like fate.</i>

00:01:25.470 --> 00:01:27.940
<i>Then we went to the beach on a trip.</i>

00:01:27.940 --> 00:01:29.530
Let's do this!

00:01:29.530 --> 00:01:30.820
Yeah!

00:01:31.750 --> 00:01:33.860
<i>We held a barbecue at the beach.</i>

00:01:34.590 --> 00:01:36.870
<i>The training we did was tough,</i>

00:01:36.870 --> 00:01:40.330
<i>but it was fun spending
time with everyone there.</i>

00:01:40.780 --> 00:01:42.450
<i>We did squats on the beach,</i>

00:01:42.580 --> 00:01:44.580
<i>push-ups on the beach,</i>

00:01:44.700 --> 00:01:46.980
<i>and Twister on the beach.</i>

00:01:47.090 --> 00:01:48.920
<i>We even took our quizzes on the beach.</i>

00:01:48.920 --> 00:01:50.960
Why do we have to do this on the beach?!

00:01:52.390 --> 00:01:55.090
<i>And tomorrow is our festival.</i>

00:01:52.960 --> 00:01:55.090
{\an7}Fall Twinkle
Series Fan Festival

00:01:55.500 --> 00:01:58.550
Here, here, and here…

00:02:00.020 --> 00:02:02.780
I wonder what the most efficient
way to see everything is…

00:02:03.450 --> 00:02:05.590
<i>Suzuka-san is all excited, too.</i>

00:02:12.700 --> 00:02:17.920
Do you hear the fanfare as
we race towards the finish?

00:02:17.920 --> 00:02:24.450
I want to see that shining future with you

00:02:26.500 --> 00:02:32.790
{\an8}Umamusume

00:02:28.370 --> 00:02:32.670
{\an8}Pretty Derby

00:02:34.680 --> 00:02:40.400
If we just start to run, that's
where our story will begin

00:02:40.400 --> 00:02:45.420
It's always waiting right in front of us

00:02:45.420 --> 00:02:51.030
If you reach out just a little
more, we can seize that glory

00:02:51.030 --> 00:02:57.890
Aim for the top, challenge
them all, and it's off to the races

00:02:58.700 --> 00:03:03.890
Even the goddess of victory will be dazzled

00:03:03.890 --> 00:03:11.170
By your big debut that's just around the bend

00:03:11.170 --> 00:03:16.590
So can you hear the fanfare
as we race towards the finish?

00:03:16.590 --> 00:03:22.060
I want to see that shining future with you

00:03:22.060 --> 00:03:27.570
Let's overtake them all! It's
a track laid out just for you!

00:03:27.570 --> 00:03:35.330
Your dreams are at the finish if you believe

00:03:37.020 --> 00:03:41.030
{\an8}Race 6

00:03:37.020 --> 00:03:41.030
{\an8}Autumn Skies and Horse Girls

00:03:46.030 --> 00:03:48.790
{\an8}Fan Festival
Twinkle Series

00:03:49.860 --> 00:03:51.940
Let's all have fun together today, okay?

00:03:51.940 --> 00:03:52.800
Of course!

00:03:52.800 --> 00:03:57.920
<i>We will now begin our
Autumn Twinkle Series Fan Festival.</i>

00:03:54.040 --> 00:03:57.920
{\an8}Fan Festival
Twinkle Series

00:03:58.450 --> 00:04:01.050
<i>Please enjoy your time here.</i>

00:04:01.050 --> 00:04:02.930
It's the president's voice!

00:04:02.930 --> 00:04:03.760
Teio-san?

00:04:03.760 --> 00:04:05.620
Spe-chan, I'll talk to you later.

00:04:05.620 --> 00:04:07.140
President!

00:04:06.430 --> 00:04:07.140
Huh?

00:04:07.140 --> 00:04:09.850
You're the coolest!

00:04:10.660 --> 00:04:13.310
We were all supposed to
spend time together…

00:04:12.890 --> 00:04:13.310
All right!

00:04:13.310 --> 00:04:17.820
{\an8}GoldShi Lunches

00:04:13.690 --> 00:04:15.350
We're going to make tons of money today.

00:04:15.350 --> 00:04:17.170
You look cute and get customers.

00:04:17.170 --> 00:04:17.820
Hmm?

00:04:17.820 --> 00:04:20.200
Huh? Why do I have to do this…

00:04:20.200 --> 00:04:21.300
Let go of me!

00:04:21.300 --> 00:04:24.850
I want to have fun with everyone!

00:04:24.850 --> 00:04:27.210
Now, where should we start?

00:04:27.210 --> 00:04:29.330
I'm checking out all of them.

00:04:29.330 --> 00:04:31.010
Can you keep up with me?

00:04:31.010 --> 00:04:31.970
What was that?!

00:04:31.970 --> 00:04:34.170
I'm going to beat you!

00:04:33.180 --> 00:04:36.020
{\an8}Hey! That's a false start!

00:04:37.170 --> 00:04:39.130
Everyone's leaving…

00:04:39.130 --> 00:04:42.200
Spe-chan, let's go.

00:04:42.200 --> 00:04:44.300
You get the most out of
a festival by having fun.

00:04:46.650 --> 00:04:47.550
Right!

00:04:47.550 --> 00:04:50.060
{\an8}Shaved Ice

00:04:47.550 --> 00:04:50.060
{\an9}Superball

00:04:52.730 --> 00:04:55.230
{\an8}Choco Carrots

00:04:52.730 --> 00:04:55.230
{\an9}Takoyaki

00:04:55.230 --> 00:04:57.730
{\an8}Kiddie Expedition Team

00:04:57.730 --> 00:05:00.570
All right, everyone! Follow me!

00:04:57.730 --> 00:05:00.000
{\an9}Hishi Amazon

00:05:02.100 --> 00:05:03.730
You look like you're having fun.

00:05:03.730 --> 00:05:05.570
You didn't want to do this at first.

00:05:05.570 --> 00:05:06.500
Wh-What?

00:05:06.500 --> 00:05:09.240
Well, you look like you're having fun, too!

00:05:09.240 --> 00:05:11.790
But I never said I didn't want to do this.

00:05:09.280 --> 00:05:11.790
{\an9}Narita Brian

00:05:13.970 --> 00:05:15.120
One down!

00:05:15.120 --> 00:05:15.910
The next one is over there!

00:05:16.480 --> 00:05:18.820
{\an8}So fast!

00:05:17.670 --> 00:05:19.820
Why are they running?

00:05:19.820 --> 00:05:22.130
Because it's fun.

00:05:22.130 --> 00:05:25.010
{\an9}Fan Festival
Twinkle Series

00:05:23.230 --> 00:05:25.010
{\an7}Rigil
Butler Café

00:05:27.110 --> 00:05:28.840
Welcome back.

00:05:27.610 --> 00:05:28.840
{\an8}Air Groove

00:05:29.510 --> 00:05:32.850
Let us toast to our destined union.

00:05:31.240 --> 00:05:32.850
{\an8}T. M. Opera O

00:05:32.850 --> 00:05:36.850
Let us spend this miraculous time together.

00:05:35.250 --> 00:05:36.850
{\an8}Fuji Kiseki

00:05:36.850 --> 00:05:38.350
Miss.

00:05:41.610 --> 00:05:43.820
I think it was this shop…

00:05:43.820 --> 00:05:44.440
Oh!

00:05:45.700 --> 00:05:46.450
Miss,

00:05:47.570 --> 00:05:49.780
here's your Royal Earl Grey.

00:05:48.180 --> 00:05:49.780
{\an7}Symboli Rudolf

00:05:51.030 --> 00:05:53.330
The president is too cool!

00:05:53.330 --> 00:05:54.820
Hey, everyone! Look!

00:05:54.820 --> 00:05:56.330
The president is so cool, isn't she?

00:05:56.330 --> 00:05:57.970
President!

00:05:59.330 --> 00:06:01.340
{\an8}Mis-fortune Telling

00:06:01.340 --> 00:06:03.230
{\an7}Matikanefukukitaru

00:06:01.340 --> 00:06:03.230
{\an3}Meisho Doto

00:06:06.970 --> 00:06:09.680
Your luck for today…

00:06:10.050 --> 00:06:11.010
…is terrible!

00:06:11.010 --> 00:06:12.810
T-Terrible?!

00:06:13.650 --> 00:06:15.640
Can't we save her somehow?

00:06:15.640 --> 00:06:17.580
Like keeping a lucky item on you.

00:06:19.550 --> 00:06:21.740
You need yakisoba!

00:06:21.740 --> 00:06:22.820
Yakisoba?

00:06:22.820 --> 00:06:26.250
McQueen, help me out again!

00:06:26.250 --> 00:06:28.530
There's too many people,
and we're not selling…

00:06:28.530 --> 00:06:31.460
Looks like the yakisoba came to you.

00:06:32.260 --> 00:06:33.890
Again?

00:06:33.890 --> 00:06:35.830
I guess I'll have to help you out.

00:06:35.830 --> 00:06:37.450
{\an8}G1 Fried Carrots

00:06:37.450 --> 00:06:40.790
Suzuka, let's work hard
at the next Mainichi Okan.

00:06:37.450 --> 00:06:39.600
{\an7}Eishin Flash

00:06:37.450 --> 00:06:39.600
{\an9}Nice Nature

00:06:41.200 --> 00:06:42.420
Yes.

00:06:42.420 --> 00:06:45.110
I'm honored to be able to run with you.

00:06:45.110 --> 00:06:47.260
H-Honored? That's too much.

00:06:47.260 --> 00:06:51.230
{\an8}I feel pretty good about this next one.

00:06:48.450 --> 00:06:52.730
<i>A lot of people talk to Suzuka-san.
She's really great.</i>

00:06:51.900 --> 00:06:56.140
{\an8}The 33rd Eating Grand Prix
is coming to an end!

00:06:54.140 --> 00:06:56.140
{\an6}Shocker! Eating Competition

00:06:54.140 --> 00:06:56.140
{\an6}Fan Festival

00:06:56.140 --> 00:06:57.680
Oguri Cap is in the lead!

00:06:57.680 --> 00:06:59.350
Followed by Super Creek.

00:06:59.390 --> 00:07:02.120
{\an8}Super Creek

00:07:00.990 --> 00:07:03.060
<i>The real battle starts after we get half way.</i>

00:07:03.060 --> 00:07:05.400
{\an8}Oguri Cap

00:07:03.900 --> 00:07:05.440
<i>This is good.</i>

00:07:05.440 --> 00:07:11.550
Who will win the prize,
this giant stuffed donut?

00:07:05.440 --> 00:07:09.900
{\an4}Grand Prize

00:07:06.360 --> 00:07:08.740
{\an9}Inari One

00:07:12.070 --> 00:07:14.890
{\an7}Tamamo Cross

00:07:12.990 --> 00:07:14.410
<i>That's Ogurin for you.</i>

00:07:14.410 --> 00:07:16.210
<i>She's called a big eater for a reason.</i>

00:07:16.210 --> 00:07:16.790
<i>But…</i>

00:07:17.980 --> 00:07:18.910
<i>But…</i>

00:07:19.500 --> 00:07:22.130
<i>I really, really want that plushie!</i>

00:07:22.130 --> 00:07:25.460
Tamamo Cross is starting to catch up!

00:07:25.460 --> 00:07:27.470
<i>I would expect no less from Tamamo Cross-san,</i>

00:07:27.470 --> 00:07:28.670
<i>but I can still do this!</i>

00:07:28.670 --> 00:07:29.880
<i>I can do this!</i>

00:07:29.880 --> 00:07:31.760
They're fighting for the lead!

00:07:32.970 --> 00:07:33.930
<i>These are good.</i>

00:07:33.930 --> 00:07:36.810
<i>I win!</i>

00:07:38.900 --> 00:07:42.640
Oh my! Tamamo Cross and Oguri Cap have
raised their hands at the same time!

00:07:40.550 --> 00:07:41.960
{\an8}I couldn't do this.

00:07:41.960 --> 00:07:42.640
{\an8}What was that?!

00:07:42.640 --> 00:07:44.860
Hold on a second!

00:07:44.860 --> 00:07:46.610
{\an6}Judge

00:07:44.860 --> 00:07:46.610
{\an8}Deliberations

00:07:45.300 --> 00:07:48.320
The judges have signaled that
they're going to deliberate!

00:07:48.320 --> 00:07:52.650
We would like to check the video record
to determine the winner.

00:07:48.320 --> 00:07:52.650
{\an8}Deliberations

00:07:52.650 --> 00:07:55.200
{\an8}Fan Festival
Twinkle Series

00:07:53.020 --> 00:07:55.200
What happened?

00:07:55.200 --> 00:07:59.130
The contestants wait with bated breath.

00:08:01.700 --> 00:08:07.450
Super Creek has thrown donuts
onto Oguri Cap's plate!

00:08:07.450 --> 00:08:09.200
There did seem to be a bit much.

00:08:09.200 --> 00:08:10.130
A bit?!

00:08:10.460 --> 00:08:13.820
Super Creek has been eliminated
due to her interference.

00:08:13.820 --> 00:08:14.890
Okay…

00:08:15.210 --> 00:08:19.400
Oguri-san, I'm sorry for
giving you the donuts.

00:08:19.400 --> 00:08:22.860
I'm sorry for eating your donuts, too.

00:08:24.390 --> 00:08:29.310
Oguri Cap has won the 33rd Eating Grand Prix!

00:08:24.390 --> 00:08:30.360
{\an8}Shocker! Eating Competition

00:08:24.390 --> 00:08:30.360
{\an8}Fan Festival

00:08:30.750 --> 00:08:32.580
I lose…

00:08:32.580 --> 00:08:34.110
Tamamo Cross…

00:08:37.030 --> 00:08:37.450
Here.

00:08:38.160 --> 00:08:39.260
What's going on?

00:08:39.860 --> 00:08:41.540
I…

00:08:41.860 --> 00:08:44.670
I just wanted to eat some donuts.

00:08:48.940 --> 00:08:50.920
Ogurin!

00:08:49.630 --> 00:08:52.840
{\an8}Fan Festival

00:08:50.920 --> 00:08:52.840
Don't call me "Ogurin."

00:08:53.270 --> 00:08:56.180
You're so nice…

00:08:56.180 --> 00:08:58.680
Sounds like you wanted
to join in, too, Spe-chan.

00:09:03.410 --> 00:09:05.240
That's so good!

00:09:05.240 --> 00:09:07.220
I can't have more than one, though.

00:09:07.220 --> 00:09:09.900
We start training again tomorrow.

00:09:09.900 --> 00:09:13.250
Grass-chan, the Mainichi Okan is going
to be your comeback race, right?

00:09:13.250 --> 00:09:18.230
Yes, I'm excited to get
to run with Suzuka-san.

00:09:18.230 --> 00:09:19.370
I'm excited, too.

00:09:19.870 --> 00:09:22.930
I might not be able to run
with you next year, after all.

00:09:24.950 --> 00:09:29.620
Um, Suzuka-san, what do you mean,
you might not be able to run next year?

00:09:30.330 --> 00:09:33.380
I was going to tell you
when things settled down,

00:09:33.900 --> 00:09:36.880
but I'm thinking of trying my luck overseas.

00:09:36.880 --> 00:09:38.760
O-Overseas?!

00:09:38.760 --> 00:09:40.260
Oh my.

00:09:40.620 --> 00:09:45.370
I need to win races here in
this country first, but…

00:09:46.150 --> 00:09:48.480
Sorry for telling you while
we're eating like this.

00:09:48.480 --> 00:09:50.900
It's okay. It's your future.

00:09:51.970 --> 00:09:54.860
<i>Suzuka-san's going to continue forward…</i>

00:09:54.860 --> 00:09:57.680
<i>I'm always watching her from behind.</i>

00:09:57.680 --> 00:09:59.950
Suzuka-san, a winner in top form.

00:09:59.950 --> 00:10:02.090
Grass, a junior champion.

00:10:04.460 --> 00:10:06.410
I'm joining the race, too, then!

00:10:06.930 --> 00:10:08.180
What?!

00:10:08.180 --> 00:10:10.510
I want to be the best in
the world. That's my goal.

00:10:10.510 --> 00:10:13.260
For that, I need to beat the two of you!

00:10:13.260 --> 00:10:15.050
M-Me, too, then!

00:10:15.050 --> 00:10:17.310
You're going to be in
the Kikkashou, aren't you?

00:10:17.310 --> 00:10:19.050
Oh yeah, that's right…

00:10:19.440 --> 00:10:21.550
<i>I'm going to be champion…</i>

00:10:22.030 --> 00:10:24.060
<i>I'm going to catch up to everyone.</i>

00:10:24.530 --> 00:10:26.560
<i>I need to focus.</i>

00:10:27.220 --> 00:10:28.340
<i>Lucky…</i>

00:10:28.340 --> 00:10:29.770
Hey.

00:10:30.430 --> 00:10:31.980
We did it.

00:10:32.630 --> 00:10:34.330
We went everywhere.

00:10:34.330 --> 00:10:35.980
Are you okay, you two?

00:10:35.980 --> 00:10:39.040
We might be more tired now
than when we're training.

00:10:39.040 --> 00:10:41.650
That's finally over.

00:10:41.650 --> 00:10:43.370
I'm tired of making money.

00:10:42.610 --> 00:10:43.370
You're tired, too?!

00:10:43.370 --> 00:10:47.030
I didn't expect that it would have
been okonomiyaki, not yakisoba.

00:10:47.030 --> 00:10:48.380
I'm so unlucky.

00:10:48.380 --> 00:10:50.840
I'll get you something sometime.

00:10:50.840 --> 00:10:52.170
Hey, everyone.

00:10:52.820 --> 00:10:53.550
What do you think?

00:10:53.550 --> 00:10:54.690
Do I look good?

00:10:54.690 --> 00:10:56.460
Teio-san, you look cool!

00:10:56.460 --> 00:10:57.170
Yay.

00:10:57.170 --> 00:11:00.090
That's the butler outfit
from Rigil's café, right?

00:11:00.090 --> 00:11:02.970
I got them to let me try it out.

00:11:03.530 --> 00:11:05.970
Now everyone, let us go home together.

00:11:06.420 --> 00:11:08.980
You've basically betrayed us.
What are you talking about?

00:11:08.980 --> 00:11:11.730
You cheater!

00:11:08.980 --> 00:11:14.370
Ow, ow, ow!

00:11:11.730 --> 00:11:14.370
Come back to Spica!

00:11:14.360 --> 00:11:29.000
{\an8}Ow, ow, ow, ow, ow, ow…

00:11:14.370 --> 00:11:17.170
<i>I'd better get out of here
while I have the chance.</i>

00:11:17.170 --> 00:11:18.820
Hey, what are you thinking?

00:11:18.820 --> 00:11:21.490
How can you tell what I'm thinking?

00:11:28.990 --> 00:11:31.780
Let go of me, already!

00:11:33.950 --> 00:11:36.330
That was fun, Spe-chan.

00:11:36.330 --> 00:11:37.650
Yeah.

00:11:39.370 --> 00:11:40.370
Thank you.

00:11:40.370 --> 00:11:40.970
Huh?

00:11:41.550 --> 00:11:43.910
I didn't really do anything!

00:11:45.590 --> 00:11:50.660
I haven't really talked with people
since I joined this school.

00:11:51.830 --> 00:11:55.310
But I think I've changed a lot
since you came here.

00:11:55.310 --> 00:11:57.360
R-Really?

00:11:57.830 --> 00:11:58.820
Yeah.

00:12:02.270 --> 00:12:07.700
Ever since I was young, I've always
felt something while I'm running.

00:12:08.900 --> 00:12:14.170
I want to keep that sparkling green
before me, and never take my eyes off it.

00:12:14.770 --> 00:12:18.270
I had so much fun running, but then…

00:12:19.860 --> 00:12:22.870
Every time I trained hard or raced,

00:12:23.340 --> 00:12:25.390
it stopped feeling like that.

00:12:29.540 --> 00:12:33.390
But I didn't want to give
up on running being fun.

00:12:34.250 --> 00:12:37.470
I wanted to see that
beautiful green again.

00:12:40.030 --> 00:12:44.490
So I thought I might be able
to find it again with Spica.

00:12:45.610 --> 00:12:47.490
Suzuka-san…

00:12:47.900 --> 00:12:50.120
Rigil is a good team, too,

00:12:50.120 --> 00:12:52.510
but with the way things
are now, running is fun again.

00:12:53.210 --> 00:12:57.000
That's why I've wanted to enter more races.

00:12:57.590 --> 00:12:59.800
So that's why you want to go overseas…

00:13:00.390 --> 00:13:02.980
I'm having a lot of fun now.

00:13:04.000 --> 00:13:10.074
